tenant Commander David L  Williams  U S   Navy  on Sept  11  2001  during the terrorist attack on the Pentagon  where he worked for the Joint Chiefs of Staff  Lieutenant Commander Williams matriculated from Herndon  Va  and earned a bachelor s degree in English from VMI  where he wore academic stars during his first class year  A three year member of the Cadet newspaper staff  he served as the newspaper s editor during his first class year  He was a member of the track team during his fourth class year  He was posthumously awarded the Meritorious Service Medal and a Purple Heart  A memorial service was held at Fort Myer  Va  on Sept  28  2001  Among his survivors are his wife  Sara Heath Williams of Arlington  Va  who is expecting their third child  two daughters  Sophie Ann and Meredith  his father and stepmother of Newport  Ore  his mother and stepfather  a sister  Becky Williams Urbanski  and a brother  Patrick Williams  The Class of 1991 established a David Williams Memorial Fund to assist the family Lieutenant Commander Williams left behind    VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 